{
  "stem": "9730.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It-- it-- it could be relatively easy, and it could be extremely hard.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sometimes some of the prisoners wanted to ingratiate themselves also with us and-- and-- and would appear to give information rather freely, whereas others, and especially some of the SS troops, were a lot harder to break down.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we really had no time to-- to-- to stay with them for a-- for a very long time and to do interrogation in depth, because the battle conditions didn't allow that.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We tried to get the-- the-- the information immediately of use to us and our troops.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and that we normally were able to get.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the prisoners were brought in, of course, by-- by our troops to-- to our, you know, regimental headquarters.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this being summer, it was no problem about housing them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had-- we had regular enclosures for them that our MPs had made for just that purpose, in whatever place we happened to be.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but from those positions, they would soon thereafter be evacuated to the rear, where they had real prisoner-of-war enclosures.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, not-- not this early.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But later on, toward the end of the war, our troops brought in someone.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and when I asked, you know, where he had been, he-- he said, well, he had been in Berlin in recent times.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I-- when I pressed him for further information, he quite readily admitted that he was, in fact, Hitler's chauffeur, had been in the bunker in which Hitler and Eva Braun committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That in fact, Hitler had called him in to give him instructions as to how to dispose of their bodies.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And those instructions, he said, he carried out to the letter.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
